{
  "texts": [
    "They utilized deep learning-based models, such as LSTM and GRU, stacked with FastText embeddings, and also implemented a transformer-based BERT model using the Hugging Face tokenizer.",
    "Among these models, BERT emerged as the most accurate, achieving a notable accuracy score of 0.73.",
    "A similar approach was undertaken by Mehta et al. [42], where they applied traditional ML algorithms, SVM, MNB, RF, LR, and DL-based model LSTM and the transformer-based BERT model.",
    "Among these, LSTM emerged as the most effective, achieving an impressive accuracy score of 0.98.",
    "After reviewing the existing literature, we conclude that many studies addressed HS using traditional ML and DL-based methods for online data."
  ]
}